    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Newark</placeName>
                <date>March 15<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1855</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir!</p>
            <p>I have delayed to inform you before as I<lb/> expect to send to you the money for your<lb/>
                <sic>Periotical</sic>, but as I could not collect it<lb/> all yet I have to inform
                you, as fellow<lb/>
                <persName>Isidor Lehman</persName> payd to me $1.75 and<lb/> gave it up to have it
                for the next year,<lb/> also <add>?</add> but have not<lb/> payd their Bill yet he
                promis' &amp; yesterday<lb/> to call and pay it. <persName>Louis Frier</persName> is
                in<lb/> such circumstances that he can't at<lb/> present and <sic>promist</sic> by
                    <sic>bether</sic> times<lb/> but did not say any <sic>Ding</sic>
                <sic>els</sic>
                <sic>abut</sic> it<lb/> to <persName>J. Hern</persName> I gave the Bill but has not
                payd<lb/> it yet, so soon <persName>Dellelbach</persName> will pay<lb/> me I shall
                sent you all I have with<lb/> my dues also- making. $1.75 from
                    <persName>Lehman</persName></p>
            <p> 1.25 H<add>?</add></p>
            <p><hi rend="underline"> 3.00 fr</hi>om my self</p>
            <p>$6.00</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I remain your</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><sic>Respectfull</sic> friend</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">Joseph Cohen</persName>
            </p>
            <p>I shall send of our circulars</p>
            <p>to the <add>?</add> in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> if can do some for us
                    <sic>pleas</sic> be so kind.</p>
        </body>
    </text>
